,Recommended,220740,32774829,Posted: 25 June,all,IMuthaTuckerI,"Great game, the first one was better though. Looking forward to playing the 3rd one soon. One thing that I found hilarious wasThe ""Lost"" series implementation with Hurley's infamous lottery numbers 4, 8, 15, 16, 23, 42. Brought a great nostalgic chuckleHowever, there was two things that really grinded my gears on this one. The first one beinghow in order to get into the resistance clubhouse, you had to turn down the actual music volume in the main menu options.How exactly is anyone supposed to figure that out without glancing at a walkthrough? I enjoy clever puzzles, but that was just too farfetched of an idea. I was searching everywhere for a solution, and was absolutely furious when I had to resort to a guide for the first time for something so silly.The second one was simply a glitch, but yet again♥♥♥♥♥♥♥♥me off that I had to use a guide again to solve it (I hate using walkthroughs for puzzle games). The part whereYou have to place the transmitter on the radio tower. I had already figured out what needed to be done without talking to Goal, so I had already placed the pool down and filled it, gave her the umbrella, and put the tree air fresheners on it. Then, when trying to hand her the lotto ticket, Rufus will say ""hmm...that still needs work."" So in order for her to take the bloody thing, I had to ask her to move out of the pool, and just ask her the steps to a thunderstorm. She finally took it after finishing all dialogues and moving her back into the pool.I just thought that was kinda dumb that I had to trigger the dialogue in order to complete that part. Again, that had me stumped for almost an hour just trying to figure out what went wrong.So, other than those two absolutely ridiculous situations, the game was fun."
