ysiums that he so wanted to be a part of? It was only until the end where he realized that a change is needed for him to be in the right. He realized that the person he should be admiring the entire time should actually be the everyday, caring people that he surrounds himself with, including his own true love which he is determined to find once more and correct himself in her eyes. It will only be then when he can live without the shadow of his own pathetic whining ego crying in the deepest recesses of his mi-PFFFFFFFT. NAH. JUST MAKE HIM ACT LIKE A JERK AGAIN!WHO NEEDS THAT PESKY CHARACTER DEVELOPMENT?! AM I RIGHT?! WE'LL GET THERE IN PART 3!"
