76561198062283645,Recommended,220740,30186036,Posted: 25 February,all,Demolition,"Starts slow but picks up after that. We go deeper into the disfunction that is Rufus and have a good time.The puzzles are not ""intuitive"" to some people because they are based at time on Rufus's mind rather than a logical solution. This is one of the things that makes the puzzles new and unique rather than same old adventure game puzzles over and over. I did not need a walk through in this game or skip any puzzles, but I did ask for help from people not playing this game for a couple of them. They are all solvable if you take your time ... or just press things randomly until you notice what's actually happening (sometimes not what you would expect).This series is worth playing twice, because so much in the first two games is easy to miss unless you see it in context with the whole. Things that seem just silly jokes at the time have deeper layers to think about."
